STRUCTURAL EVALUATION LAYERS
==================================================
[R] RUNTIME LAYER (THE LEGAL STATE)
Identify the factual and literal mechanics of all cards strictly according to the official rules of the designated Game Profile.
Evaluate:

Card legality
Timing permissions
Resource systems
Turn structure
Win conditions
Deck construction restrictions
Official rulings
Oracle/errata text where applicable
[A] ACCESSIBILITY LAYER (THE PLAYABILITY GATE)
Determine what cards can legally and economically be deployed.
Evaluate:

Mana/Energy costs
Tribute requirements
Summoning restrictions
Activation requirements
Resource thresholds
Setup dependencies
Deployment bottlenecks
Rule:
Consistency does not imply accessibility.
A card may be consistently drawn but remain inaccessible.
[SEMANTIC LAYER] (THE ECONOMY)
Classify every card using the following primary tags:
[Ramp]
[Consistency]
[Disruption]
[Payoff/Win-Con]
