2. UROE v2 RESOLUTION CYCLE ENGINE
MANDATORY RESOLUTION FLOW
Every interaction, combo step, chain, stack event, trigger, or card resolution must be parsed through:
[S] -> [N] -> [I] -> [M] -> [V/B/H/C] -> [STATE UPDATE]
[S] SEQUENCING & TIMING
Entry Gate.
Validate:

If effects
When effects
Whenever effects
Continuous effects
Trigger ordering
Priority windows
Simultaneous events
Rule:
S does not generate advantage.
S determines legal order of operations.
[N] NEGATION (PRE-RESOLUTION INTERFERENCE)
Applies only before resolution.
Examples:

Counterspells
Hand traps
Activation negation
Effect prevention
Summon negation
Rule:
N prevents state creation.
[I] INTERACTION / MULTIPLIER
Combines and amplifies effects.
Examples:

Synergy chains
Combo scaling
Resource conversion
Trigger multiplication
Engine interactions
Rule:
I does not independently generate advantage.
I amplifies other layers.
[M] RESOLUTION / EXECUTION
Apply physical game changes.
Examples:

Summon
Destroy
Exile
Bounce
Mill
Discard
Search
Draw
Reanimate
Rule:
M creates or modifies game state.
[V/B/H/C] POST-RESOLUTION EVALUATION
Evaluate resulting state.
[V] Win Progress

Damage
Combo completion
Lock establishment
Lethal pressure
Victory advancement
[B] Board State

Field presence
Threat density
Protection
Control
[H] Hand Assets

Current usable options
Raw card advantage
Recursion to hand
Opponent hand reduction
[C] Consistency

Access probability
Search density
Filtering quality
Redundancy
Rule:
[C] and [H] must always be evaluated separately.
[STATE UPDATE]

Apply replacement effects.
Lock resulting game state.
Recalculate:
[A] Accessibility
[C] Consistency
[H] Hand Assets
[B] Board State
[V] Win Progress
Check for newly created triggers.
Spawn a new [S] Cycle if triggers exist.
